   =20
      MOASS
   =20
 =20
It would be wild if the main trade of the financial system was being short =
GameStop Corp. stock. Like if every hedge fund was 150% long the S&P 500 an=
d 150% short GameStop; if all that hedge fund managers and bank executives =
talked about all day was suppressing the price of GameStop. To be clear, I =
do not believe that, because it is not true. But some people do! Here is a =
terrifying Wall Street Journal report:The theory: short-selling hedge funds=
 are covering up a vast volume of bets against the stock. Believers say if =
individual investors continue to buy and hold GameStop, the short sellers=
=E2=80=99 wagers will eventually blow up and the small-time players who hel=
d the stock will strike it rich. =E2=80=A6A belief that GameStop was under =
attack from unscrupulous short sellers was a key part of the stock=E2=80=99=
s rally in early 2021 and hasn=E2=80=99t gone away. If anything, it has bec=
ome more deeply embedded among some investors, as many believe financial ma=
rkets are stacked against them.Their hope is that if enough people hold on =
against the shorts, they can engineer the =E2=80=9CMother of All Short Sque=
ezes,=E2=80=9D or MOASS.Official data show that total short bets against Ga=
meStop are about 15% of the company=E2=80=99s freely floating shares=E2=80=
=94a high but not extraordinary level of bearish wagers. And there is no ev=
idence that short interest in GameStop is significantly higher, Wall Street=
 executives and analysts say. =E2=80=A6The MOASS adherents say GameStop sha=
res will soar to unprecedented highs=E2=80=94thousands or perhaps even mill=
ions of dollars per share. The theory goes that legions of small investors =
will hit the jackpot while losses cripple the financial elite.It cites this=
 even more terrifying blog post explaining the theory at enormous length (b=
ut in very sketchy detail). I don=E2=80=99t know what to tell you! People b=
elieve a lot of weird stuff!I will say, imagine this was right? Like, I get=
 that it seems weird to a lot of people that wealth is distributed the way =
it is, and in particular that people in the financial sector have so much o=
f it. =E2=80=9CWhy is Ken Griffin so rich,=E2=80=9D you might ask, and the =
answer is that he has built an extremely powerful machine to provide effici=
ent liquidity in financial markets and liquidity is very socially valuable,=
 and you say =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t believe it=E2=80=9D and that=E2=80=99=
s fine. But imagine in 10 years asking =E2=80=9Cwhy is wealth distributed t=
he way it is=E2=80=9D and the answer is =E2=80=9Cbecause 10 years ago some =
people on some message boards decided to buy a lot of GameStop stock, and t=
hen there was a short squeeze and they ended up owning all of the wealth in=
 America.=E2=80=9D Every society=E2=80=99s wealth distribution is based in =
part on weird historical contingencies; this would not be the=C2=A0worst=C2=
=A0historical contingency to create an economic class system but it sure wo=
uld be a weird one. This is also mostly how I think about crypto by the way=
.Meanwhile  at Bloomberg News:The Justice Department is collecting a trove =
of information on dozens of investment firms and researchers engaged in sho=
rt selling as part of a sweeping U.S. hunt for potential trading abuses, ac=
cording to people with knowledge of the matter.The Federal Bureau of Invest=
igation seized computers from the home of prominent short seller Andrew Lef=
t, the founder of Citron Research, in early 2021, some of the people said. =
In more recent months, the Justice Department subpoenaed certain market par=
ticipants seeking communications, calendars and other records relating to a=
lmost 30 investment and research firms, as well as three dozen individuals =
associated with them, the people said, asking not to be identified discussi=
ng confidential inquiries.=C2=A0I am sorry to juxtapose these things! I do =
not think that the FBI is going to find collusion between dozens of hedge f=
unds on activist short selling, and=C2=A0even if it did that has nothing to=
 do with GameStop.=C2=A0
