</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse Group AG lends a lot of =
money to a lot of different customers for a lot of different things. If you=
 want undifferentiated diversified exposure to all of those different loans=
, you can buy Credit Suisse stock (which gives you risky equity exposure)=
=C2=A0or bonds (safer senior exposure), or deposit your money at Credit Sui=
sse=E2=80=99s bank (very safe super-senior exposure).</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Or you can skip all the mortgages, small-business loans, corpora=
te lines of credit etc., and buy direct exposure to only the finest handpic=
ked yacht loans. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/26626731.270615/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMWEwOWQ0ZTYtZTNkNi00=
